#: src/components/HeatAdaptationPanel.tsx:151
#~ msgid "Heat adaptation covers acclimatization from natural heat and acclimation from controlled heat, but this tracker observes only outdoor connector weather; treadmill and indoor summary weather are discarded. It uses one activity-summary temperature/humidity pair. Environmental evidence takes the stronger of an estimated 18–26°C Stull psychrometric wet-bulb ramp at standard sea-level pressure and an estimated 30–40°C dry-bulb ramp; the ramps are never added and this is not WBGT. Outside Stull's 5–99% RH domain, only the dry-bulb ramp can contribute. Work minutes at or above 50% of a same-provider current CP are weighted by the stronger ramp, using timestamped samples when they cover at least 90% of activity duration and splits otherwise. Sample gaps over five seconds do not count toward coverage. A session counts at 30 effective minutes. Within a rolling 14-day window, 2 days and 60 effective minutes indicate Building; 7 days and 420 effective minutes indicate Likely adapted. The environmental ramps, effective minutes, stage thresholds, and the 7–28 day decay window are Praxys operational estimates; evidence labels describe data coverage, not biological certainty. Wind, solar radiation, within-session weather changes, clothing, hydration state, and measured core or skin temperature are excluded. Repeated exposure can reduce cardiovascular and thermal strain, but individual response varies and female-specific evidence remains limited. This is not medical clearance or a current heat-risk assessment: follow Today's signal, keep normal hydration and cooling available, stop immediately and begin cooling for heat-illness symptoms, and seek urgent medical help for confusion, collapse, or altered mental status."
#~ msgstr "热适应涵盖自然热环境下的热习服（acclimatization）和受控热环境下的热习服（acclimation），但本追踪器只采集室外连接器天气；跑步机和室内活动的摘要天气会被丢弃。它使用一组活动摘要温湿度。环境证据取两条估算线性权重坡度中较强者：在标准海平面气压下 18–26°C 的 Stull 估算湿球温度坡度，以及 30–40°C 的干球温度坡度；二者不会相加，结果也不是 WBGT。超出 Stull 的 5–99% 相对湿度适用范围时，只有干球温度坡度可贡献证据。达到同一提供方当前 CP 50% 及以上的训练分钟，会按较强的环境坡度加权；时间戳样本覆盖至少 90% 活动时长时使用样本功率，否则使用分段功率。超过 5 秒的样本间隔不计入覆盖率。单次训练达到 30 个加权分钟才计入。在滚动 14 天窗口内，2 天且 60 个加权分钟表示“建立中”；7 天且 420 个加权分钟表示“可能已适应”。环境权重坡度、加权分钟、阶段阈值和 7–28 天衰减窗口均为 Praxys 的操作性估算；证据标签描述数据覆盖度，不代表个体生理适应的确定性。模型不包含风速、太阳辐射、训练过程中的天气变化、服装、补水状态，以及实测核心体温或皮肤温度。反复热暴露可降低心血管和热应激，但个体反应不同，针对女性的证据仍有限。这不构成医疗许可，也不评估当前热风险：请遵循今日信号，保持正常补水并准备降温措施；一旦出现热病症状，应立即停止热暴露并开始降温；如出现意识混乱、虚脱或精神状态改变，应立即寻求紧急医疗救助。"

